{
  "video_id": "yL4VLsdxrN0",
  "title": "Poetry that frees the soul (with English subtitles) | Cristina Domenech",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Sebastian Betti Reviewer: Gisela Giardino"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14963.0,
      "end_time": 17988.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s said that to be a poet"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 18948.0,
      "end_time": 22553.0,
      "text": "you have to go to hell and back."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24173.0,
      "end_time": 27348.0,
      "text": "The first time I visited the prison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27349.0,
      "end_time": 32250.0,
      "text": "I was not surprised by the noise of the padlocks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 32250.0,
      "end_time": 36242.0,
      "text": "or the closing doors, or the cell bars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 36243.0,
      "end_time": 40246.0,
      "text": "or by any of the things I had imagined."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 40246.0,
      "end_time": 45559.0,
      "text": "Maybe because the prison is in a quite open space."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 45559.0,
      "end_time": 47689.0,
      "text": "You can see the sky."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 47689.0,
      "end_time": 51332.0,
      "text": "Seagulls fly overhead, and you feel like you&#39;re next to the sea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 51332.0,
      "end_time": 54375.0,
      "text": "that you&#39;re really close to the beach."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 54375.0,
      "end_time": 60305.0,
      "text": "But in fact, the gulls are looking for food in the dump near the prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 61250.0,
      "end_time": 67221.0,
      "text": "I went farther inside and I suddenly saw inmates moving across the corridors."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 67886.0,
      "end_time": 71966.0,
      "text": "Then it was as if I stepped back and thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 71966.0,
      "end_time": 75774.0,
      "text": "that I could have very well been one of them."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 75775.0,
      "end_time": 81522.0,
      "text": "If I had another story, another context, different luck."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 82457.0,
      "end_time": 87958.0,
      "text": "Because nobody - nobody - can choose where they&#39;re born."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 89790.0,
      "end_time": 94453.0,
      "text": "In 2009, I was invited to join a project"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 94453.0,
      "end_time": 99860.0,
      "text": "that San Martín National University conducted at the Unit 48 penitentiary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 99865.0,
      "end_time": 103800.0,
      "text": "to coordinate a writing workshop."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 103800.0,
      "end_time": 109525.0,
      "text": "The prison service ceded some land at the end of the prison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 109525.0,
      "end_time": 115157.0,
      "text": "which is where they constructed the University Center building."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 116152.0,
      "end_time": 118570.0,
      "text": "The first time I met with the prisoners,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 118570.0,
      "end_time": 122244.0,
      "text": "I asked them why they were asking for a writing workshop"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 122245.0,
      "end_time": 125896.0,
      "text": "and they told me they wanted  to put on paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 125896.0,
      "end_time": 129827.0,
      "text": "all that they couldn&#39;t say and do."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 131620.0,
      "end_time": 135929.0,
      "text": "Right then I decided that I wanted poetry to enter the prison."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 137434.0,
      "end_time": 141380.0,
      "text": "So I said to them why don&#39;t we work with poetry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 141440.0,
      "end_time": 142780.0,
      "text": "if they knew what poetry was."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 143375.0,
      "end_time": 148267.0,
      "text": "But nobody had a clue what poetry really was."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 150622.0,
      "end_time": 152256.0,
      "text": "They also suggested to me"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 152256.0,
      "end_time": 154775.0,
      "text": "that the workshop should be not just for the inmates"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 154775.0,
      "end_time": 160310.0,
      "text": "taking university classes,  but for all the inmates."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 160641.0,
      "end_time": 163808.0,
      "text": "And so I said that to start this workshop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 163808.0,
      "end_time": 167650.0,
      "text": "I needed to find a tool that we all had in common."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 167650.0,
      "end_time": 170756.0,
      "text": "That tool was language."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 170756.0,
      "end_time": 176948.0,
      "text": "We had language, we had the workshop. We could have poetry."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 176948.0,
      "end_time": 182774.0,
      "text": "But what I hadn&#39;t considered was that inequality exists in prison, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 182774.0,
      "end_time": 187895.0,
      "text": "Many of the prisoners hadn&#39;t even completed grammar school."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 187895.0,
      "end_time": 193275.0,
      "text": "Many couldn&#39;t use cursive, could barely print."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 195410.0,
      "end_time": 199820.0,
      "text": "They didn&#39;t write fluently, either."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 199820.0,
      "end_time": 203692.0,
      "text": "So we started looking for short poems."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 203693.0,
      "end_time": 206759.0,
      "text": "Very short, but very powerful."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 206759.0,
      "end_time": 210506.0,
      "text": "And we started to read, and we&#39;d read one author, then another author,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 210507.0,
      "end_time": 215982.0,
      "text": "and by reading such short poems, they all began to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 215982.0,
      "end_time": 220639.0,
      "text": "that what the poetic language did was to break a certain logic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 220639.0,
      "end_time": 222394.0,
      "text": "and create another system."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 222394.0,
      "end_time": 225988.0,
      "text": "Breaking the logic of language also breaks the logic of the system"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 225988.0,
      "end_time": 229755.0,
      "text": "under which they&#39;ve learned to respond."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 230550.0,
      "end_time": 234430.0,
      "text": "So a new system appeared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 234430.0,
      "end_time": 239202.0,
      "text": "new rules that made them understand very quickly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 239202.0,
      "end_time": 241810.0,
      "text": "- very quickly -"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 241810.0,
      "end_time": 243230.0,
      "text": "that with poetic language"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 243230.0,
      "end_time": 247738.0,
      "text": "they would be able to say absolutely whatever they wanted."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 251479.0,
      "end_time": 256570.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s said that to be a poet you have to go to hell and back."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 257475.00000000003,
      "end_time": 261974.00000000003,
      "text": "And they have plenty of hell. Plenty of hell."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 261974.0,
      "end_time": 266589.0,
      "text": "One of them once said: \"In prison you never sleep."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 266589.0,
      "end_time": 271454.0,
      "text": "You can never sleep in jail. You can never close your eyelids.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 272351.0,
      "end_time": 278707.0,
      "text": "And so, like I’m doing now, I gave them a moment of silence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 278707.0,
      "end_time": 283429.0,
      "text": "then said, “That&#39;s what poetry is, you guys."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 284309.0,
      "end_time": 289494.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s in this prison universe that you have all around you."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 289494.0,
      "end_time": 291774.0,
      "text": "Everything you say about how you never sleep,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 291774.0,
      "end_time": 293464.0,
      "text": "it exudes fear."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 293464.0,
      "end_time": 298229.0,
      "text": "All the things that go unwritten -- all of that is poetry.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 299469.0,
      "end_time": 303676.0,
      "text": "So we started appropriating that hell;"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 303676.0,
      "end_time": 307183.0,
      "text": "we plunged ourselves, headfirst, into the seventh circle."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 307184.0,
      "end_time": 311222.0,
      "text": "And in that seventh circle of hell, our very own, beloved circle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 311222.0,
      "end_time": 315433.0,
      "text": "they learned that they could make the walls invisible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 315434.0,
      "end_time": 317604.0,
      "text": "that they could make the windows yell,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 317604.0,
      "end_time": 320544.0,
      "text": "and that we could hide inside the shadows."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 323504.0,
      "end_time": 327464.0,
      "text": "When the first year of the workshop had ended,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 327464.0,
      "end_time": 329872.0,
      "text": "we organized a little closing party,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 329872.0,
      "end_time": 333562.0,
      "text": "like you do when a job is done with so much love,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 333562.0,
      "end_time": 336512.0,
      "text": "and you want to celebrate with a party."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 336512.0,
      "end_time": 340979.0,
      "text": "We called family, friends,  the university authorities."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 340979.0,
      "end_time": 345320.0,
      "text": "The only thing the inmates had to do was read a poem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 345321.0,
      "end_time": 347558.0,
      "text": "and receive their diplomas and applause."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 347558.0,
      "end_time": 350850.0,
      "text": "That was our simple party."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 352105.0,
      "end_time": 357400.0,
      "text": "The only thing I want to leave you with"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 358694.0,
      "end_time": 363190.0,
      "text": "is the moment in which those men,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 363190.0,
      "end_time": 365514.0,
      "text": "some of them just huge when standing next to me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 365519.0,
      "end_time": 371230.0,
      "text": "or the young boys - so young, but with an enormous pride,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 371230.0,
      "end_time": 377730.0,
      "text": "held their papers and trembled like little kids and sweated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 377780.0,
      "end_time": 382287.0,
      "text": "and read their poems with their voices completely broken."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 384420.0,
      "end_time": 388800.0,
      "text": "That moment made me think a lot"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 388959.0,
      "end_time": 393660.0,
      "text": "that for most of them, it was surely the very first time"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 393660.0,
      "end_time": 397563.0,
      "text": "that someone applauded them for something they had done."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 400809.0,
      "end_time": 404262.0,
      "text": "In prison there are things that can&#39;t be done."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 404262.0,
      "end_time": 409118.0,
      "text": "In prison, you can&#39;t dream. In prison, you can&#39;t cry."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 409118.0,
      "end_time": 414147.0,
      "text": "There are words that are virtually forbidden, like the word \"time,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 414147.0,
      "end_time": 419150.0,
      "text": "the word \"future,\" the word \"wish\"."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 419160.0,
      "end_time": 424322.0,
      "text": "But we dared to dream, and to dream a lot."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 424322.0,
      "end_time": 429126.0,
      "text": "We decided that they were going to write a book."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 429126.0,
      "end_time": 433546.0,
      "text": "Not only did they write a book, but they also bound it themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 433546.0,
      "end_time": 436642.0,
      "text": "That was at the end of 2010."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 436642.0,
      "end_time": 441510.0,
      "text": "Then, we doubled the bet and wrote another book."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 441510.0,
      "end_time": 442685.0,
      "text": "And we bound that one, too."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 442685.0,
      "end_time": 446109.0,
      "text": "That was a short time ago, at the end of last year."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 448474.0,
      "end_time": 452000.0,
      "text": "What I see week after week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 452000.0,
      "end_time": 456357.0,
      "text": "is how they&#39;re turning into different people;"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 456357.0,
      "end_time": 458904.0,
      "text": "how they&#39;re being transformed."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 458904.0,
      "end_time": 463251.0,
      "text": "How words are empowering them with a dignity they had never known,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 463251.0,
      "end_time": 465334.0,
      "text": "that they couldn&#39;t even imagine."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 465334.0,
      "end_time": 470125.0,
      "text": "They had no idea such dignity could come from them."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 471130.0,
      "end_time": 478397.0,
      "text": "At the workshop, in that beloved hell we share, we all give something."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 478397.0,
      "end_time": 482997.0,
      "text": "We open our hands and hearts and give what we have, what we can."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 482997.0,
      "end_time": 485151.0,
      "text": "All of us; all of us equally."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 485151.0,
      "end_time": 489766.0,
      "text": "And so you feel that at least in a small way"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 489766.0,
      "end_time": 493416.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re repairing that huge social fracture"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 493416.0,
      "end_time": 498634.0,
      "text": "which makes it so that for many of them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 498634.0,
      "end_time": 501812.0,
      "text": "prison is their only destination."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 504172.0,
      "end_time": 509551.0,
      "text": "I remember a verse by a tremendous poet, a great poet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 510586.0,
      "end_time": 516430.0,
      "text": "from our Unit 48 workshop, Nicolás Dorado:"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 520395.0,
      "end_time": 526789.0,
      "text": "\"I will need an infinite thread to sew up this huge wound.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 527485.0,
      "end_time": 532679.0,
      "text": "Poetry does that; it sews up the wounds of exclusion."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 533400.0,
      "end_time": 538242.0,
      "text": "It opens doors.  Poetry works as a mirror."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 538417.0,
      "end_time": 541762.0,
      "text": "It creates a mirror, which is the poem."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 541762.0,
      "end_time": 545744.0,
      "text": "They recognize themselves, they look at themselves in the poem"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 545745.0,
      "end_time": 550808.0,
      "text": "and write from who they are, and are from what they write."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 550808.0,
      "end_time": 553513.0,
      "text": "In order to write,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 553513.0,
      "end_time": 557704.0,
      "text": "they need to appropriate the moment of writing"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 557704.0,
      "end_time": 561155.0,
      "text": "which is a moment of extraordinary freedom."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 561155.0,
      "end_time": 564980.0,
      "text": "They have to get into their heads, search for that bit of freedom"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 564980.0,
      "end_time": 569123.0,
      "text": "that can never be taken away when they write"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 569124.0,
      "end_time": 572635.0,
      "text": "and that is also useful to realize that freedom is possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 572635.0,
      "end_time": 574973.0,
      "text": "even inside a prison,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 574973.0,
      "end_time": 580234.0,
      "text": "and that the only bars we have in our wonderful space"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 580235.0,
      "end_time": 582970.0,
      "text": "is the word \"bars,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 582970.0,
      "end_time": 585959.0,
      "text": "and that all of us in our hell burn with happiness"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 585959.0,
      "end_time": 589669.0,
      "text": "when we light the wick of the word."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 589669.0,
      "end_time": 592669.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 617143.0,
      "end_time": 623597.0,
      "text": "I told you a lot about the prison, a lot about what I experience"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 623597.0,
      "end_time": 628178.0,
      "text": "every week, and how I enjoy it and transform myself with the inmates."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 628178.0,
      "end_time": 631593.0,
      "text": "But you don&#39;t know how much I&#39;d like it"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 631593.0,
      "end_time": 637159.0,
      "text": "if you could feel, live, experience, even for a few seconds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 637159.0,
      "end_time": 641494.0,
      "text": "what I enjoy every week and what makes me who I am."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 644151.0,
      "end_time": 647151.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 653228.0,
      "end_time": 657459.0,
      "text": "Martín Bustamante:  The heart chews tears of time;"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 657464.0,
      "end_time": 660346.0,
      "text": "blinded by that light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 660346.0,
      "end_time": 663721.0,
      "text": "it hides the speed of existence"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 663721.0,
      "end_time": 665874.0,
      "text": "where the images go rowing by."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 665874.0,
      "end_time": 668847.0,
      "text": "It fights; it hangs on."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 668847.0,
      "end_time": 672549.0,
      "text": "The heart cracks under sad gazes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 672554.0,
      "end_time": 676327.0,
      "text": "rides on storms that spread fire,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 676327.0,
      "end_time": 679451.0,
      "text": "lifts chests lowered by shame,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 679451.0,
      "end_time": 682627.0,
      "text": "knows that it&#39;s not just reading and going on,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 682627.0,
      "end_time": 686452.0,
      "text": "it also wishes to see the infinite blue."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 686457.0,
      "end_time": 690185.0,
      "text": "The heart sits down to think about things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 690185.0,
      "end_time": 692896.0,
      "text": "fights to avoid being ordinary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 692897.0,
      "end_time": 696320.0,
      "text": "tries to love without hurting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 696320.0,
      "end_time": 700230.0,
      "text": "breathes the sun, giving courage to itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 700230.0,
      "end_time": 704391.0,
      "text": "surrenders, travels toward reason."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 704391.0,
      "end_time": 707294.0,
      "text": "The heart fights among the swamps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 707294.0,
      "end_time": 710819.0,
      "text": "skirts the edge of the underworld,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 710819.0,
      "end_time": 715101.0,
      "text": "falls exhausted, but won&#39;t give in to what&#39;s easy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 715101.0,
      "end_time": 717590.0,
      "text": "while irregular steps of intoxication"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 717590.0,
      "end_time": 719167.0,
      "text": "wake up,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 719167.0,
      "end_time": 721570.0,
      "text": "wake the stillness."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 721570.0,
      "end_time": 723290.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m Martín Bustamante,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 723756.0,
      "end_time": 727254.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m a prisoner in Unit 48 of San Martín,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 727254.0,
      "end_time": 730112.0,
      "text": "today is my day of temporary release."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 730112.0,
      "end_time": 733784.0,
      "text": "And for me, poetry and literature have changed my life."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 733784.0,
      "end_time": 734905.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much!"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 734905.0,
      "end_time": 736324.0,
      "text": "Cristina Domenech: Thank you!"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 736325.0,
      "end_time": 738645.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}